                            <comment id="485978" author="JIRAUSER20209" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2026 10:42:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&apos;ve added some test code for verification. It seems basic IPv6 over IB functionality is working correctly, and IPv6 CM connections are establishing successfully.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did also notice a limitation for kiblnd: the IB spec limits private data to 56 bytes during rdma_connect. Our current `kib_msg + kib_connparams` already uses the full 56 bytes, so we can&apos;t simply extend it from NID4 to NID16 to elegantly support IPv6. This is a kiblnd design challenge, not an IB issue, so we can discuss solutions as we move forward.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 56-byte limit comes from:&lt;br/&gt;
56B = 92B (CM REQ PrivateData) - 36B (IP CM Header)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
